# Free AI Check CLI — environment keys.
#
# EVERY key is optional: any missing key just skips that data source and the run
# continues (the report notes what was skipped). Set the ones you have.
# Copy this file to `.env`, fill it in, and load it before running, e.g.:
#   set -a; . ./.env; set +a
# Never commit your real .env. Keys are never printed by the CLI.

# --- Claude: drafts the one-page report (Opus 4.8) -------------------------
# https://console.anthropic.com  →  API Keys
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# --- Layer A: what the AI engines actually say ----------------------------
# Perplexity — best value; returns the answer AND the sources it cited.
# https://www.perplexity.ai  →  Settings  →  API
PERPLEXITY_API_KEY=

# OpenAI — ChatGPT-with-web-search proxy (Responses API).
# https://platform.openai.com  →  API keys
# If you get a 400 on the web-search tool, your account may need the tool name
# "web_search_preview" instead of "web_search" — see src/gather/openai.ts.
OPENAI_API_KEY=

# Google Gemini — Google AI proxy, with Search grounding.
# Google AI Studio:  https://aistudio.google.com/app/apikey
# NOTE: this is a DIFFERENT key/product from GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY below.
GEMINI_API_KEY=

# --- Layer B: Google Business Profile + website speed ---------------------
# A Google CLOUD CONSOLE key. In APIs & Services > Library, enable:
#   - "Places API (New)"  (service: places.googleapis.com)  REQUIRED for Layer B
#       profile, reviews, hours, categories — must be the NEW one, not legacy "Places API"
#   - "PageSpeed Insights API"  (service: pagespeedonline.googleapis.com)  OPTIONAL
#       mobile speed. NOTE: PageSpeed also works WITHOUT a key (just rate-limited),
#       the key only raises the quota. Not "Analytics Hub" — that's unrelated.
# https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials
GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY=
